In large saucepan, saute olive oil, garlic, onion, green pepper and celery until vegetables are tender. Add ground beef and 1-1/2 teaspoons Morton(R) Hot Salt(TM). Cook until ground beef is browned. Drain fat. Add Bush's Best(R) chili beans in sauce, diced tomatoes, water, chili powder and remaining 1-1/2 teaspoons Morton(R) Hot Salt(TM). Bring to boiling; reduce heat. Cover and simmer for 15 minutes, stirring occasionally. Serve with shredded Cheddar cheese and sour cream, if desired.